ship networks tend to have higher market power as measured by markup. In addition, markup is negatively associated with a firm's propensity to export, its likelihood of product upgrade, and the chance of survival in foreign markets. Our findings have policy implications on antitrust regulations and competitiveness policies, especially in export-oriented economies dominated by powerful business conglomerates.\"));\n}\n;\nMDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;","fields":{"slug":"/dp/140/common-ownership-domestic-competition-and-export-evidence-from-thailand/","collection":"dp","shorturl":"/dp/140/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Common Ownership, Domestic Competition, and Export: Evidence from Thailand","subtitle":null,"series":null,"authors":["Tosapol Apaitan","Chanont Banternghansa","Archawa Paweenawat","Krislert Samphantharak"],"date":"2020-06-08T00:00:00.000Z","updated":null,"cover":null,"excerpt":null,"bibliography":null,"topics":null,"tags":null,"layout":null,"pdf":{"publicURL":"/static/1c75ae2a54b0283fafa2f5077c181a61/pier_dp_140.pdf"}},"authors":[{"frontmatter":{"memberid":"Archawa Paweenawat","title":"Archawa Paweenawat","org":"pier","email":"ArchawaP@bot.or.th","image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/dd515/profile.jpg","srcSet":"/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/6ac16/profile.jpg 50w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/e07e1/profile.jpg 100w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/dd515/profile.jpg 200w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/47930/profile.jpg 400w","sizes":"(min-width: 200px) 200px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/dbc4a/profile.webp 50w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/d8057/profile.webp 100w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/2e34e/profile.webp 200w,\n/static/a83d60ff1f5b67fb20898027c58a0a1e/416c3/profile.webp 400w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min